Hi, my name is Rayan

I'm a web developer from Ottawa





Staight out of HighSchool I worked as a IT in the Government of Canada under a 1 year contract. After the year my contract was suppose to get extended but due to covid I was dismissed. Fortunately the Governement had something for the people who lost there Jobs and offered money till the individual found a job. So at the time I was getting bored at my mom's house. My dad was working at Oracle at the time and told me to learn to code and told me that he could've offered me a position at his company as a software Developer. I thought why not and I decided to learn Python. After studying the basics I realize that I was not applying these skills to nothing. I was literally creating functions and creating small games. I remember telling my self that I would not be able to do nothing with just knowing the syntax and couple of functions. So I decided to apply to a coding bootcamp. That's when my real coding journey started!
